DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds permanently the nominal current. The maximal current you can request until this error happens, is two times the nominal current is requested for 5s.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Continuous overcurrent (total DC link out current)
DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds permanently the nominal current. The maximal current you can request until this error happens, is two times the nominal current is requested for 5s.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Continuous overcurrent. Output: %u. Reaction: Generative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds permanently the nominal current. The maximal current you can request until this error happens, is two times the nominal current is requested for 6s.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Continuous overcurrent (total DC link out current). Reaction: Generative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds permanently the nominal current. The maximal current you can request until this error happens, is two times the nominal current is requested for 6s.
The demanded current from axis system overloads the power supply module. This happens when a current higher than two times the nominal current is requested.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Peak overcurrent (total DC link out current)
DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system overloads the power supply module. This happens when a current higher than two times the nominal current is requested.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Short circuit (total DC link out current)

DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds the parameterized warning threshold.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Continuous overcurrent (total DC link out current)
DiagMessage.Description: The demanded current from axis system exceeds the parameterized warning threshold.
The actual mains voltage exceeds the parameterized mains voltage (0x8000:06) by more than 20% or by more than the parameterized positive tolerance (0x8000:07), if this higher than 20%.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The actual mains voltage is too high.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Look for an allowed mains voltage.

DiagMessage.Description: One phase is failed by 3-phase-supply.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is faulty.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analyze the mains voltage supply and resolve the problem.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is disturbed over and over.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Activate a filter, which effects, that the phase monitoring waits longer, until this error is set.

CauseRemedy.Cause: You use the power supply module in a one-phase-mains but it is parametrized for three phases. And the module has not recognized the mains type properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type and correct its value. Switch on again the mains voltage.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Mains voltage over brake resistor operating voltage
DiagMessage.Description: The mains voltage has voltage peaks that causes the brake chopper to be switched on.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Voltage peaks occur by the mains voltage.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize the mains supply and make, that the voltage peaks do not happen.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The parametrization of DC link max voltage (0x8000:01) is too low.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your application and parametrize the DC link max voltage higher, if necessary. In this case the switchOn threshold voltage (0x9006:0C) of the brake chopper should has been changed.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Mains phase failure. Reaction: Generative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: One phase is failed by 3-phase-supply for longer than 10s.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is faulty.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analyze the mains voltage supply and resolve the problem.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains voltage supply is disturbed over and over.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Activate a filter, which effects, that the phase monitoring waits longer, until this error is set.

CauseRemedy.Cause: You use the power supply module in a one-phase-mains but it is parametrized for three phases. And the module has not recognized the mains type properly.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type and correct its value. Switch on again the mains voltage.

DiagMessage.Description: The connected mains type (3Ph/AC, 1Ph/AC or DC) does not match with parameterized value of mains type (0x8000:04).

CauseRemedy.Cause: Mains type is parameterized with wrong value.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the parameter Mains type and correct its value.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The mains supply is not connected right.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the mains supply and connected it right, Switch on the mains voltage again.

DiagMessage.Description: The connected mains voltage exceeds the parameterized warning threshold.
The connected mains voltage fell below the parameterized warning threshold.
The DC link voltage rises over the permitted DC link voltage because of power feedback (brake) from the motors.
The DC link voltage rises over the permitted maximal DC link voltage because of power feedback (brake) from the motors.

DiagMessage.MessageText: DC link overvoltage with Torque off
DC link undervoltage with Torque off

DiagMessage.Description: The device temperature exceeds the permitted maximal value of 80,0C.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your application has produced a thermic overload of the power supply module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this thermic overload does not happen.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Excess temperature device: %s. Reaction: Generative brake order
DiagMessage.Description: The device temperature exceeds the permitted maximal value of 80,0C.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Your application has produced a thermic overload of the power supply module.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Analize your application and make, that this thermic overload does not happen.

DiagMessage.Description: The actual device temperature exceeds the parameterized warning threshold.
An error occurred while reading data from the eeprom during initialization.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An internal hard- or software failure happened, while reading data from eeprom.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: An error occurred while reading data from the eeprom during initialization. - ID 0: PowerPcb - ID 1: LinkPcb - ID 2: OptionPcb - ID 3: DisplayPcb

CauseRemedy.Cause: A internal hard- or software failure happened, while reading data from eeprom.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.MessageText: %s E2PROM device address is incompatible to this Firmware
%s Firmware Index is incompatible to this Firmware
DiagMessage.Description: Detected incompatible Pcb for this Firmware. - ID 0: PowerPcb - ID 1: LinkPcb - ID 2: OptionPcb - ID 3: DisplayPcb

CauseRemedy.Cause: This Hardware needs a newer Firmware.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Ask the Beckhoff branch office that is responsible for you for the right Firmwareversion.

DiagMessage.MessageText: %s Structure Version is incompatible to this Firmware
%s Component Type is incompatible to this Firmware
Product is incompatible to this Firmware
Update BIC to SII Eeprom failed: %s

DiagMessage.Description: The persistent memory contains an errorlog. The messages are restored during power on phase.
A timeout has occurred.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An unknown software failure happened.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: An error in the internal configuration has occurred.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The firmware update was not succesfully.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again and start a new firmware update. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: Default values of parameters could not be loaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Device ids or power board ids are missing in eeprom.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: A parameterization error has occurred.
Brake chopper failured.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Brake chopper is damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: Your connected brake resistor (internal or external) was overloaded.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Current at connected brake resistor is too high. The brake resistor may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Check whether your brake resistor is damaged, if external one connected. Try to operate power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.Description: No connected brake resistor can be detected.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Internal brake resistor is faulty and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch on them again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is missing and any external brake resistor has not been connected.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Plug in the connection bridge or connect an external brake resistor.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The connection bridge for the internal brake resistor is not pugged in, an external brake resistor has been connected but this may be damaged.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check your external brake resistor. If this is not damaged, try to operate the power supply module again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Brake resistor power overload by DC link overvoltage
DiagMessage.Description: Brake resistor was disabled because of power overload.
Device description file does not match to device or to firmware.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by firmware update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file.

CauseRemedy.Cause: Wrong file by device description update choosen.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Start again a firmware update with the right file. A separate device description update is not necessary because this is made automatically by a firmware update.

CauseRemedy.Cause: The firmware or device description files do not match to device.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Check the files. Change them or change the device, if necesary.

DiagMessage.Description: The brake resisor load utilization exceeds the parameterised warning threshold.
Failure at I2C bus.

CauseRemedy.Cause: An I2C-member is hanging and a reset of the I2C-bus failed.
CauseRemedy.Remedy: Switch off the mains voltage and the 24V-supply. Switch them on again. If this error happens repeatedly, please contact your Beckhoff office.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Data Collector %s version is incompatible to this Firmware
Error reaction forced: Generative brake order
Error reaction forced: Non-generative brake order
Error reaction forced: Brake chopper off
Error reaction forced: Torque Off order
Error reaction forced: NC handling order
Load resistor overloaded with error reaction brake
DiagMessage.Description: Dc link load resistor exceeds the permitted range of 65%.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Load resistor overloaded with error reaction torque off
DiagMessage.Description: Dc link load resistor exceeds the permitted range of 90%.

DiagMessage.MessageText: Fan malfunction. Reaction: Generative brake order
Debug firmware, replace "As soon as possible"!
DiagMessage.Description: Debug fimware: Replace ASAP!
